{
  "name": "Geo-Spoon",
  "type": "equipment",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>A wooden tablespoon that looks to be carved from wild cherry. It puts a new meaning to the saying \"eat my dust!\" It allows for the safe practice of <em>Geophagia</em>.</p><p>When ash, dirt, gravel or similar compounds are scooped with this spoon, after one minute the material becomes edible but it does nothing to improve the taste.</p><p>This food is comparable to a <strong>ration</strong> and must be eaten out of the spoon<em>. </em>After each usage roll a d6, and on a 1 the spoon ceases to make ash, dirt, gravel, etc; edible until the next dawn.</p>",
